{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "22", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "21", "M": "53", "S": "47"}}, "news": [{"title": "New buildings, boundary walls found on protected forest land in Anangpur despite SC curbs", "para": "Fresh construction, including a multi-storey building and boundary walls, has emerged in Anangpur village's protected forest belt, a PLPA-notified area. This development occurs despite Supreme Court interventions and findings of thousands of illegal structures in the Aravalis. Experts warn that such activity fragments the ecosystem, disrupts groundwater recharge, and blocks wildlife corridors, signaling continued pressure on this ecologically vital region.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/illegal-construction-in-anangpurs-protected-forest-supreme-court-interventions-ignored/131900949?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2964024/131900949.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Jaipur development body turns to direct plot auctions to boost revenue", "para": "In response to a real estate slump, the Jaipur Development Authority (JDA) is now directly auctioning residential plots to end buyers, a departure from its previous investor-centric approach. This strategic shift aims to boost auction participation and revenue by offering vacant plots in schemes like Vipra Vihar and Bilwa. The JDA plans to extend these direct sales to several other housing projects, targeting individual homebuyers.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/jaipur-development-authority-introduces-direct-plot-auctions-to-stimulate-housing-market/131900933?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-224838/131900933.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Over 260 LEDs to rescue Panchkula villages from permanent nights", "para": "Panchkula's rural residents are set to receive much-needed street lighting as the development and panchayat department has tendered \u20b911.72 lakh for 261 LED lights across ten villages.  This initiative aims to curb night-time accidents and deter wild animals, addressing long-standing safety concerns.  Years of administrative delays are finally being overcome with a fresh, streamlined tender, bringing relief to communities who have actively campaigned for this essential infrastructure.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/lighting/outdoor-lighting/transforming-panchkula-villages-261-led-street-lights-for-safer-nights/131900921?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-245428/131900921.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "lighting"}]}